      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 135: The edition loop stores `edBody` after applying `bodyOverwrite`, so the original/raw edited body is lost in `previousBodies`. That conflicts with the new `OriginalBody` role, which needs unmodified content for edit mode. Preserve the raw edition body separately from the display body, or avoid overwriting `previousBodies` if it is used as source-of-truth for editing.\n```suggestion\nconst auto rawBody \u003d edition.value(\"body\");\nauto displayBody \u003d rawBody;\nif (const auto boIt \u003d edition.find(\"bodyOverwrite\"); boIt !\u003d edition.end() \u0026\u0026 !boIt.value().isEmpty())\n    displayBody \u003d boIt.value();\n// Store rawBody for editing and displayBody for rendering, using separate fields/roles.\n```",
      "revId": "95e6b4d10e3f35b3ce717f7bf2ed66e7048d0532",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
