      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 528: `OriginalBody` returns `commit[\"body\"]`, which appears to be the first/original committed body, not necessarily the current editable body after message editions. Editing an already-edited plugin-overwritten message may therefore prefill stale text instead of the latest raw message content. Please derive this role from the latest edition\u0027s raw `body` when editions exist, falling back to the commit body only when there are no editions.\n```suggestion\ncase Role::OriginalBody: {\n    if (!item.second.previousBodies.isEmpty())\n        return QVariant(item.second.previousBodies.last().body);\n    if (item.second.commit.contains(\"body\"))\n        return QVariant(item.second.commit.value(\"body\"));\n    return QVariant(item.second.body);\n}\n```",
      "revId": "95e6b4d10e3f35b3ce717f7bf2ed66e7048d0532",
